title: Real VOCA Basic
subtitle: 14일이면 한 권을 충분히 볼 수 있습니다.

contents.text: I hear a noise.
It's my alarm clock going off.
The alarm clock goes off at 7 o'clock.
I'm still asleep in my cozy bed.
contents.translation: 나는 여전히 아늑한 침대에서 자고 있다.

contents.text: I make toast for breakfast.
I toast two slices of bread.
Oops! I smell burnt toast.
I burned the toast.
I fry eggs for breakfast.
I like fried eggs sunny-side up.
But my sister likes fried eggs over easy.
contents.translation: 하지만 내 여동생은 양면을 살짝 익힌 계란을 좋아한다.

contents.text: I make orange juice for breakfast.
I juice two oranges.
contents.translation: 나는 오렌지 두 개의 즙을 짠다.

contents.text: I put oranges and a spoonful of honey into the blender.
contents.translation: 나는 오렌지와 꿀 한 숟가락을 블렌더에 넣는다.

contents.text: I press the power button on the blender.
I pour some milk into a large bowl.
I microwave it for 2 minutes.
The microwave beeps.
I warm up milk for my dog.
contents.translation: 나는 우리 강아지를 위해 우유를 데운다.

contents.text: I enjoy my great breakfast.
Oops! I spill a cup of juice.
contents.translation: 앗! 나는 주스 한 잔을 흘렸다.

contents.text: The toast soaks up the juice.
The tablecloth gets soaked with the juice.
The dog licks up the juice that spilled on the floor.
My sister skips breakfast.
She doesn't have enough time to eat.
She'll pick up a latte instead.
I need to pee.
I take a leak.
I squeeze some toothpaste onto my toothbrush.
I squeeze the tube in the middle.
I brush my teeth.
I brush my teeth clean.
I floss my teeth.
I gently floss my teeth with dental floss.
I wash my face.
I wash my face with cold water.
I wipe my face.
I dry my face with a towel.
I shampoo my hair.
I get some in my eyes.
I apply conditioner then rinse it with water.
contents.translation: 나는 컨디셔너를 바른 다음 물로 헹군다.

contents.text: I dry my hair with a towel.
I dry my hair with a hairdryer.
I comb my hair.
I brush my hair with a comb.
I run my fingers through my hair.
I go out of the bathroom.
Oh! I left the faucet running.
I should turn off the faucet.
I sit down in front of my dressing table.
I look at myself in the mirror.
contents.translation: 나는 거울 속 내 모습을 본다.

contents.text: I was pale last night.
After a sound sleep, I look better.
contents.translation: 푹 잔 후에 나는 더 좋아 보인다.

contents.text: I have fair skin.
I have fair smooth skin.
contents.translation: 나는 하얗고 매끄러운 피부를 가지고 있다.

contents.text: My brother has bronze skin
contents.translation: 내 형(동생)은 구릿빛 피부를 가지고 있다.

contents.text: He has bronze skin and some pimples.
contents.translation: 그는 구릿빛 피부에 여드름이 몇 개 있다.

contents.text: My skin is dry these days.
The cold weather makes my skin dry.
contents.translation: 추운 날씨 때문에 내 피부가 건조해진다.

contents.text: I apply lots of moisturizer to my face.
I apply moisturizer with a cotton ball
I put lotion on my face.
I rub it into my skin.
I apply sunscreen on my face.
I rub sunscreen into my skin.
My brother is always clean shaven.
contents.translation: 내 형(동생)은 항상 깔끔하게 면도를 한다.

contents.text: He shaves every morning.
He usually uses an electric razor to shave.
But sometimes he uses a disposable razor.
He applies shaving cream before shaving.
contents.translation: 그는 면도하기 전에 면도 크림을 바른다.

contents.text: He puts on aftershave lotion after shaving.
contents.translation: 그는 면도 후에 애프터셰이브 로션을 바른다.

contents.text: He uses a spray deodorant under his arms.
He sprays cologne on his wrists.
Will it be windy today?
Will it be cold today?
Will it be rainy today?
I'm thinking of what to wear.
I take off my pajamas.
I put on gray pants.
Oh, I feel uneasy. They're too tight.
I take off the pants.
I guess I have gained weight.
I step on the digital scale.
Oh, my! I've gained 2 kilos! I need to go on a diet.
I step off the scale.
I put on a beige skirt instead.
I put on a pair of black pantyhose.
I put on my new purple sweater.
The sweater goes with the skirt. They match really well.
contents.translation: 스웨터가 치마와 어울린다. 정말 잘 어울린다.

contents.text: I look great in the sweater and the skirt.
contents.translation: 나는 스웨터와 치마를 입으면 멋있어 보인다.

contents.text: The sweater and the skirt suit me.
Two coats are hanging in the closet.
Two scarves are hanging in the closet.
I choose the cashmere coat.
I select the mink scarf.
I slip on a pair of shoes.
I'm ready to go out!
I walk to the bus stop.
It takes 5 minutes to get there on foot.
There are lots of people at the bus stop.
They are waiting for their buses to arrive.
Finally, my bus comes along.
I get on the bus. But others are still getting on.
contents.translation: 나는 버스에 탄다. 하지만 다른 사람들은 아직도 타고 있다.

contents.text: I touch my transportation card to the reader.
The bus is less crowded than usual.
There is one empty seat over there.
Luckily, I get the empty seat.
An old lady gets on the bus.
I give up my seat.
I have to change to the subway.
It takes 10 minutes to get to the subway station by bus.
contents.translation: 버스를 타고 지하철역까지 가는 데 10분이 걸린다.

contents.text: I get off the bus.
The subway station is across from the bus stop.
I go three stations, and then I transfer to Line 2.
The subway is too crowded.
It's another 20 minutes to reach the office.
There are no empty seats.
I hold on to a strap.
I doze off.
Oh no! I missed my stop.
I get off the subway in a hurry.
Phew, I made it! Just in time for work!
I greet my colleagues with a smile.
I turn on my computer.
I turn on all the office equipment.
I check my e-mail. My inbox is full of spam.
contents.translation: 나는 이메일을 확인한다. 내 받은편지함이 스팸으로 가득하다.

contents.text: I delete the spam.
I reply to the work related e-mails.
I download a file.
The file suddenly closes.
The computer freezes.
I turn my computer off and back on again.
I find the file.
I print out the document.
The printer is out of order.
No, it's just out of paper.
I feed paper into the printer.
I take the printouts.
I shred the unnecessary documents with the shredder.
I prepare for the meeting.
Finally, I review all the material for my presentation.
contents.translation: 마침내 나는 발표를 위한 모든 자료를 검토한다.

contents.text: The meeting starts at 2 p.m I go over this week's schedule with my team.
contents.translation: 회의가 오후 2시에 시작한다. 나는 팀과 함께 이번 주 일정을 검토한다.

contents.text: Then, I give my presentation.
The meeting finishes at 4 p.m.
I need a cup of coffee.
It's almost time to call it a day.
I go for a drink twice a week.
contents.translation: 나는 일주일에 두 번 술을 마시러 간다.

contents.text: I usually go to a bar with a colleague after work.
contents.translation: 나는 보통 퇴근 후에 동료와 함께 바에 간다.

contents.text: We go to a bar called Kevin's.
It's my favorite place near the office. It's located near a busy three-way intersection.
contents.translation: 사무실 근처에 있는 내가 가장 좋아하는 곳이다. 번화한 삼거리 근처에 있다.

contents.text: They have a cocktail show with music once a week.
contents.translation: 그들은 일주일에 한 번 음악과 함께하는 칵테일 쇼를 한다.

contents.text: The show is amazing!
I get the bartender's attention.
I ask for it on the rocks.
And I want to have some nachos.
Owen, my colleague, orders his drink.
He wants a bottle of beer.
The bartender takes our order.
Owen asks for some napkins.
The bartender gives him some napkins.
He serves us our drinks.
We have a toast.
We talk about that afternoon's meeting.
contents.translation: 우리는 그날 오후 회의에 대해 이야기한다.

contents.text: We chat about the boss. Actually, Owen is stressed out recently due to the boss.
contents.translation: 우리는 상사에 대해 대화한다. 사실 오웬은 최근 상사 때문에 스트레스를 받고 있다.

contents.text: Owen drinks three more bottles of beer I drink two more Rum and Cokes. I feel good.
contents.translation: 오웬은 맥주를 세 병 더 마시고 나는 럼 앤 콜라를 두 잔 더 마신다. 기분이 좋다.

contents.text: But Owen seems to be drunk.
I go shopping at a department store.
The clothing department is on the second floor.
I go to the clothing department.
I look for a pair of jeans.
Mannequins display the new styles.
One is wearing a pair of jeans.
They look great on the mannequin.
I usually wear a size S.
I ask the clerk to find a size S.
contents.translation: 나는 점원에게 S 사이즈를 찾아달라고 요청한다.

contents.text: The clerk shows me to the fitting room.
I try on a size S.
The jeans do not fit.
They are somewhat tight.
I try on a size M.
I look great in the jeans.
contents.translation: 나는 그 청바지를 입으면 멋져 보인다.

contents.text: I check the price tag.
The jeans are 90 dollars.
They're quite expensive.
I hesitate to buy them.
Luckily, they're on sale now.
I get a 20% discount.
I pay for the jeans.
I get the receipt.
My heels are worn down.
They are loose.
I go to the shoe department.
The shoe department is on the third floor.
I look for a pair of high heels.
I prefer high heels to flats.
I look for red high heels.
I already have two pairs of black high heels.
contents.translation: 나는 이미 검은색 하이힐 두 켤레를 가지고 있다.

contents.text: I try on a size S.
The shoes fit perfectly.
I'm wondering whether they will go well with my new jeans.
contents.translation: 나는 그것들이 새 청바지와 잘 어울릴지 궁금하다.

contents.text: I'm sure they will!
I pay for the shoes.
I get the receipt.
I'm satisfied with my purchases.
I put on the new high heels at home.
They're somewhat tight.
They hurt my feet a little.
contents.translation: 그들은 내 발을 조금 아프게 한다.

contents.text: I can't wiggle my toes.
Fortunately, I didn't remove the price tag.
And I have the receipt.
I return to the shoe department.
I exchange them for a bigger size.
contents.translation: 나는 그것들을 더 큰 사이즈로 교환한다.

contents.text: There are several empty tables in the restaurant.
contents.translation: 식당에 빈 테이블이 여러 개 있다.

contents.text: I ask for a table in the non-smoking section.
I ask for a table by the window.
I sit down and take in the view.
The waiter sets the table.
I look over the menu.
I give an order for my lunch.
The waiter takes my order.
The water glass is chipped, and the plate is chipped, too!
I ask the waiter for a new glass and plate.
contents.translation: 나는 웨이터에게 새 컵과 접시를 요청한다.

contents.text: The waiter quickly replaces them.
The waiter serves the soup.
The soup is too bland.
I put some salt in the soup.
Now it is too salty.
I ordered my steak rare.
But the steak is served well-done. It is tough.
contents.translation: 하지만 스테이크가 완전히 익어 나왔다. 질기다.

contents.text: I ask the waiter to exchange the main dish.
contents.translation: 나는 웨이터에게 메인 요리를 교환해 달라고 요청한다.

contents.text: He returns later with another steak.
contents.translation: 그는 나중에 다른 스테이크를 가지고 돌아온다.

contents.text: I have cheesecake and coffee for dessert.
Fortunately, the cheesecake is delicious.
The waiter brings me the check.
I pay the check.
